is art.\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3421174 {\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546 \tab 5. To produce poetry that is hard and clear, never blurred and indefinite. \par \tab 6. Finally, most of us believe that concentration is of the very essence of poetry.\par ---Amy Lowell, Preface to }{\i\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546 Some Imagist Poets}{\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546 , 1915\par \par \par \par \par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tqr\tx9360\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3421174 {\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546 \par Modern Poetry, Imagism Image List \tab Prof. Hammer\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3421174 {\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546 \par \par Unless otherwise noted, all images reproduced from the Yale Collection of American Literature, Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library:\par \par ---Photo of H.D. with locket, c. 1915 \par \par ---Photo of H.D., c. 1935 \par \par ---Photo of H.D. in front of Sterling Library with Prof. Norman Holmes Pearson and Bryher, 1956 \par \par ---Photo of H.D. in Sterling Library, with exhibition case in honor of her seventieth birthday, 1956 \par \par ---Photo of H.D.\rquote s death mask by R. A. Stahli, 1961\par \par ---Photo of H.D., c. 1915, inscribed \ldblquote To Marianne Moore, H.D.\rdblquote \par \par ---}{\i\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546 Poetry Magazine}{\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546  1 (1912) 1; front cover \par \par ---\ldblquote Translations and Reflections from \lquote The Anthology\rquote \rdblquote  by \ldblquote H.D., Imagiste,\rdblquote  including \ldblquote Hermes of the Ways,\rdblquote  \ldblquote Priapus,\rdblquote  and \ldblquote Epigram,\rdblquote  in }{\i\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546 Poetry Magazine}{\fs24\insrsid3421174\charrsid1193546  1 (1913) 4: 120-22 \par \par ---}{\i\fs24\insrsid